# Universal Development Rules - API Development

When developing APIs, follow these comprehensive standards:

## OpenAPI Specification
- Define APIs using OpenAPI 3.0+ specifications first
- Include comprehensive request/response schemas
- Document all error responses with RFC 9457 format
- Provide example requests and responses

## RESTful Design
- Use appropriate HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH)
- Implement consistent resource naming conventions
- Apply proper HTTP status codes
- Follow HATEOAS principles where applicable

## Request/Response Handling
- Implement consistent pagination (cursor-based preferred)
- Use standardized filtering and sorting parameters
- Apply request validation with detailed error messages
- Include correlation IDs in all responses

## Performance & Scalability
- Implement response caching strategies
- Use compression for large payloads
- Apply rate limiting per client/endpoint
- Implement proper timeout handling

## Security Standards
- Validate all input parameters and payloads
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use HTTPS/TLS 1.3+ for all endpoints
- Apply CORS policies appropriately

## Error Handling
- Use RFC 9457 Problem Details format
- Provide actionable error messages
- Include error codes for programmatic handling
- Log errors with appropriate detail levels

